Response.Q11: It's really impossible to answer those questions the same for all data types. For a radily evolving and globally spreading virus, the date is critical and location perhaps not useful. For all, providing the actual sequence alignment used, and having that alignment provide links to the database (CenBank accession number, for example) is the best way to go. Providing all the information in tip labels is too much for drawing most trees to publication size and quality.
